oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Mack Vickery Studio Demos - 1967-12-07 Reel #2
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The recording is of Mack Vickery (musician). The recording features a studio recording of: "Two Old Freight Trains," "Jailbirds Can't Fly," and "Searching For Baby." The recordings were created at the Columbia Recording Studios, in Nashville, Tennessee, for Boone Records. The recording is of the unedited studio session and labeled reel number two of two. The recording takes place on December 07, 1967.
